## **What does .gitignore do?**

It tells Git to **ignore** these files/folders when pushing to GitHub. This prevents:
- ❌ OS junk files (`.DS_Store`, `Thumbs.db`)
- ❌ Editor settings (`.vscode/`, `.idea/`)
- ❌ Temporary files
- ❌ Sensitive data (`.env` files)

